  Why? Thanks to the so-called  Halloween documents, revealed by open-source co-founder Eric S. Raymond, we know exactly what Microsoft thought about Linux and open source: &#34;OSS [Open-Source Software] poses a direct, short-term revenue and  platform threat to Microsoft, particularly in server space.&#34;
